---
import SiteLayout from "@layouts/SiteLayout.astro"
import Link from "../components/Link.astro"
---

<SiteLayout>
  <header
    class="my-6 flex flex-col items-center justify-around gap-8 text-center sm:flex-row sm:gap-0 sm:text-left"
  >
    <div class="order-last sm:order-first">
      <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl font-bold">Debashis Biswas</h1>
      <p class="text-lg">Software Engineer, Musician</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <!-- Avoiding the Image component as it makes my image too blurry. -->
      <img
        src="/assets/headshot_500x500.webp"
        alt="My headshot!"
        width="256"
        height="256"
        class="rounded-lg"
      />
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="mb-12 space-y-4">
    <p>
      Hi, I'm Debashis. I'm a software engineer at Honeywell. I've previously worked at Garmin and
      Intel. I currently spend most of my time using Elixir, TypeScript, and Python, and I'm
      comfortable in other languages as well.
    </p>
    <p>
      I completed my MS in Computer Science at Arizona State University, where I primarily studied
      cybersecurity: binary analysis and exploitation, reverse engineering, and network security.
    </p>
    <ul class="list-inside list-disc leading-relaxed">
      I've recently been exploring:
      <li>real-time distributed systems for music applications</li>
      <li>design and UX</li>
      <li>infrastructure as code</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      I'm also a classically-trained clarinetist, and I completed my BMus in Clarinet Performance at
      Arizona State University. I've studied with
      <Link href="https://www.selmer.fr/en/blogs/artistes/robert-spring">Dr. Robert Spring</Link>,
      <Link href="https://www.selmer.fr/en/blogs/artistes/joshua-gardner">Dr. Joshua Gardner</Link>,
      and
      <Link href="https://www.selmer.fr/en/blogs/artistes/stefanie-gardner">
        Dr. Stefanie Gardner
      </Link>. In addition to the clarinet, I play the bass clarinet, contra-alto clarinet, and
      contrabass clarinet.
    </p>
    <p>
      Oh, and I repair musical instruments! I studied instrument repair with Dr. Steve Prescott, a
      well-known repairperson in the clarinet community. I primarily focus on clarinet repair,
      though I've done a bit of work on flutes and saxophones.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some of my other interests include calisthenics, cooking, language learning, note-taking
      systems, ergonomic keyboards, type theory, (neo)vim, Linux, and NixOS.
    </p>
    <p>
      You can find me on
      <Link href="https://github.com/debashisbiswas/">GitHub</Link>,
      <Link href="https://x.com/raenastra">Twitter</Link>, and
      <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/d-biswas/">LinkedIn</Link>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h3 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Inspirations</h3>

    <ul class="list-inside list-disc leading-relaxed">
      Here are some of my inspirations in computing:
      <li><Link href="https://github.com/josevalim">José Valim</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://slim.computer/">Slim Lim</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://thesephist.com/">Linus Lee</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://x.com/thdxr">Dax Raad</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://lexi-lambda.github.io/">Alexis King</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://geohot.com/">George Hotz</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Feynman">Richard Feynman</Link></li>
      <li><Link href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Kay">Alan Kay</Link></li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      While it's difficult to be exhaustive, here are some posts and talks that have changed my
      perspective in a meaningful way.
    </p>

    <ul class="list-inside list-disc leading-relaxed">
      <h4 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold tracking-tight">Posts</h4>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://commandcenter.blogspot.com/2012/06/less-is-exponentially-more.html">
          Less is exponentially more
        </Link>, Rob Pike
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://lexi-lambda.github.io/blog/2019/11/05/parse-don-t-validate/">
          Parse, don't validate
        </Link>, Alexis King
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://thesephist.com/posts/tools/">
          Build tools around workflows, not workflows around tools
        </Link>, thesephist
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://github.com/tigerbeetle/tigerbeetle/blob/main/docs/TIGER_STYLE.md">
          Tiger Style
        </Link>, TigerBeetle
      </li>
    </ul>

    <ul class="list-inside list-disc leading-relaxed">
      <h4 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold tracking-tight">Talks</h4>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://youtu.be/6ZdxiQoOBgs">
          History of Computers & User Interface Images & Symbols
        </Link>, Alan Kay
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://youtu.be/agkXUp0hCW8">Gang of None: Design Patterns in Elixir</Link>,
        José Valim
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://youtu.be/sC1B3d9C_sI">TigerBeetle</Link>, Joran Dirk Greef
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://youtu.be/ipRvjS7q1DI">Can machines think?</Link>, Richard Feynman
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
